    "headerDoc": "STEP 924 — Multiplicatively Perfect Number Infinitude\n  =======================================================\n\n  A number n is **multiplicatively perfect** iff the product of all\n  positive divisors of n equals n². Equivalently, τ(n) = 4 where τ\n  is the divisor-count function.\n\n  Classification: τ(n) = 4 iff either\n    (a) n = p³ for some prime p, or\n    (b) n = p · q for distinct primes p, q.\n\n  Consequence: Since there are infinitely many primes (Euclid 300 BC),\n  there are infinitely many cubes of primes p³, each multiplicatively\n  perfect. Hence **infinitely many multiplicatively perfec"
  },
